title: Analysis of SensorLog and GT3X Data
text: vignette, go steps analyze SensorLog data. go steps reading data, checking potential duplicates timestamps, calculating distance metrics fixed point (commonly participant home), creating daily summaries. also integrate ActiGraph data show activity different distances.

title: Analysis of SensorLog and GT3X Data
text: data used example data embedded waterways package. single participant approximately two hours worth GPS activity data. SensorLog data stored zip file contains single CSV file. data stored extdata folder package. can get path file user’s machines using system.file package name: can also done using wrapper waterways:
code: library(waterways) file = system.file(   "extdata", "SensorLogFiles_my_iOS_device_250311_14-55-58.zip",   package = "waterways") file #> [1] "/home/runner/work/_temp/Library/waterways/extdata/SensorLogFiles_my_iOS_device_250311_14-55-58.zip" ww_example_sensorlog_file() #> [1] "/home/runner/work/_temp/Library/waterways/extdata/SensorLogFiles_my_iOS_device_250311_14-55-58.zip"

title: Analysis of SensorLog and GT3X Data
text: data read using ww_read_sensorlog function: option robust run rewrite_sensorlog_csv run data. rewrite_sensorlog_csv attempts fix shifts data, seen due bug iOS app. option default FALSE can take much longer time read data due reading writing data back temporary file. function also flag values latitude longitude 0 (absolute value <0.00001< 0.00001). flag created iOS app sometimes record 0 latitude longitude GPS signal lost. see data following columns, renamed original data. mapping new column names original column names can seen using ww_sensorlog_csv_colnames_mapping:

title: Analysis of SensorLog and GT3X Data
text: data processed using ww_process_sensorlog function. function (currently) : Check data duplicated data using ww_check_data. Calculate distance central point provided using ww_calculate_distance Process timing data using ww_process_time, including checking duplicate times. function also determine data correct timezone estimating timezone expected (expected_timezone field, set America/New_York) based GPS coordinates, using lutz::tz_lookup_coords function. check desired, set expected_timezone = NULL: error indicates, duplicate times file. can look specific duplicate times see even 3 digits milliseconds, multiple measurements: Thus, want ensure duplicated times, set check_data FALSE: Note, argument apply_tz apply time zone data. helpful set correct time zone data absolute terms. Unfortunately, makes researchers make sure time shift things like hours. example, want find data 10AM 6PM EST time zone, need shift GMT/UTC. Also, cause issues shifts data different dates. data likely/sleep rest, can skew numbers. analysis, apply timezone: data times projected GMT timezone agree output ActiGraph read.gt3x::read.gt3x. NOTE: shifts times original timezone. example, data “2025-03-25 14:14:00” timezone -04:00 data GMT timezone, printed time “2025-03-25 18:14:00 GMT”. can set timezone correct timezone using lubridate::with_tz lubridate::force_tz (different behavior). can also pass tz = "EST" argument ww_process_sensorlog, passed ww_process_time. additional column char_time added original character values fo time retained users can check timezone conversions, can lead issues merging data, determining windows (e.g. wake), time-based analyses.

title: Analysis of SensorLog and GT3X Data
text: pass latitude longitude fixed point calculate distance processing function, . can also calculate distance separately using function ww_calculate_distance. First, need get latitude longitude fixed point. can use tidygeocoder package get latitude longitude fixed point. use address 615 N Wolfe St, Baltimore MD Johns Hopkins Bloomberg School Public Health data collected, using Census Geocoder free: can also get Census-level information using: , can construct 12-digits FIPS code GEOID10 census tract required geocoding EPA walkability index: can simply focus EPA walkability index, NatWalkInd column. can also get EPA walkability index category breaks cat_walk_index: can calculate distance fixed point using ww_calculate_distance function: function uses geosphere::distm function calculate distance meters fixed point. can see new columns added data.

title: Analysis of SensorLog and GT3X Data
text: summarize activity profile different levels proximity fixed point read GT3X data. data captured using ActiGraph (Pensacola FL) GT9X device. data stored extdata folder package, similar SensorLog data. get path via ww_example_gt3x_file: can read data using read.gt3x package, waterways wraps using ww_read_gt3x. can check timezone data using lubridate::tz function: apply_tz argument ww_read_gt3x (default) find timezone header file, apply data. done using lubridate::with_tz function. timezone stored header file, can seen using header attribute: can confirm via header: timezone stored TimeZone field. data GMT, “correct” since local time projected GMT. example, measured data timezone -04:00 read.gt3x gave value 2025-03-25 14:14:00, true time GMT 2025-03-25 18:14:00. Using read.gt3x, time incorrectly 2025-03-25 14:14:00 GMT, ww_read_gt3x 2025-03-25 18:14:00 GMT. means want convert timezones, need use lubridate::with_tz lubridate::force_tz. apply timezone information similarly SensorLog reasons discussed . can read data without applying timezone, giving “incorrect” data can merged SensorLog shift times different dates: ActiLife, ActiGraph software, values zero axes set last observation carried forward (LOCF). fill_zeroes argument (default) apply . Also, data read using read.gt3x: > DateTimes therefore represented POSIXct format ‘GMT’ timezone attribute, false; datetime actually represents local time. can calculate number summary measures acceleration. calculate ActiGraph Activity Counts using agcounts package. use epoch = 60 calculate counts 60-second epochs. counts, can estimate non-wear using Choi (Choi et al. 2011) algorithm, use actigraph.sleepr package. ww_process_gt3x perform operations together:

title: Analysis of SensorLog and GT3X Data
text: can easily manipulate time variables get date, hour, minute level data. example function create_date_hour_minute. recommend using hms data type hour minute columns. since many times want plot data hour/minute facet day: Alternatively, group data participant, can create observation day variable puts data per-person time frame (time start) versus calendar time: can plot counts time, colored within home/work (within ):  can also color distance home, much difference :
code: create_date_hour_minute = function(data) {   data = data %>%     mutate(       date = lubridate::floor_date(time, "1 day"),       date = lubridate::as_date(date),       hour = lubridate::floor_date(time, "1 hour"),       hour = hms::as_hms(hour),       minute = lubridate::floor_date(time, "1 minute"),       minute = hms::as_hms(minute)     ) } create_day = function(data) {   data = data %>%     dplyr::mutate(       day = as.numeric(difftime(date, min(date), units = "days") + 1)     ) } if (rlang::is_installed("ggplot2")) {   library(ggplot2)   data %>%      create_date_hour_minute() %>%      ggplot(aes(x = minute, y = counts)) +     geom_point(aes(colour = is_within_home)) +      geom_line() +      facet_wrap( ~ date) } if (rlang::is_installed("ggplot2")) {   library(ggplot2)   data %>%      create_date_hour_minute() %>%      ggplot(aes(x = minute, y = counts)) +     geom_point(aes(colour = distance)) +      geom_line() +      facet_wrap( ~ date) }

text: can estimate wear time using wear column ActiGraph data. calculate sum wear date: Without regard SensorLog data, can calculate wear time date. useful want see much data collected given day: calculated, can exclude dates without insufficient wear time (e.g. 95% day 1368 minutes, 10 hours wear). Different tasks require different criteria wear time.
